Package: Friedman
Title: Tools for Simple Data Exploration and Visualization
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Anuli", "Segree", email = "anuli.segree@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: 
    Friedman is an R package designed to support simple data exploration,
    cleaning, and visualization workflows for students and beginner analysts.
    The package will provide functions for summarizing datasets, checking for
    missing values, and producing clear plots for exploratory data analysis.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports: 
    ggplot2,
    dplyr
License: CC0
LazyData: true
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/AnuliSegree/Friedman
BugReports: https://github.com/AnuliSegree/Friedman/issues
